<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kokujev, 1895" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1895" box="[669,991,331,358]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Chelonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae" subGenus="Arichelonus">
<emphasis box="[669,695,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[712,736,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[753,815,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">olgae</emphasis>
Kokujev, 1895
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by the following characters: ovipositor obviously extended beyond apex of metasomal carapace and covered with a semi-round and semi-hyaline lamella (the ovipositor not or weakly projecting beyond apex of metasoma in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kokujev, 1895" authorityName="Kokujev" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Chelonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae" subGenus="Arichelonus">
<emphasis box="[1360,1386,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1403,1427,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,213,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">olgae</emphasis>
Kokujev, 1895
</taxonomicName>
); metasoma entirely brown (metasoma with pair of yellow basal spots); about 22 antennomeres of female, distinctly shorter than body length (antennomeres of female about 45, equal to body length).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="533" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1042]" box="[199,1068,511,538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[352,459,511,537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Holotype</typeStatus>
, female, length of body 
<quantity box="[730,818,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
, of fore wing 
<quantity box="[975,1064,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,547,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Head.</emphasis>
Antennomeres 22 (
<figureCitation box="[489,567,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4I</figureCitation>
); third antennomere 1.1 × longer than fourth; third, fourth and terminal antennomeres 4.0 ×, 3.5 × and 1.75 × longer than wide; head transverse, in dorsal view roundly contracted behind eyes; OOL: OD: POL=19: 15: 9; longitudinal diameter of eye 2.1 × height of temples; vertex behind ocelli and temple transversely striate; frons distinctly concave (
<figureCitation box="[669,762,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4G</figureCitation>
); face evenly convex, coarsely transversely striate; clypeus hardly convex and densely punctate, slightly shiny; length of malar space 1.5 × basal width of mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
); face and eyes densely setose in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[652,743,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,763,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Length of mesosoma 1.3 × its height; mesonotum evenly convex, irregular areolate-rugose and more strongly rugose postero-medially; scutellum hardly convex, punctate medially, rugose laterally; scutellar suture comparatively deep; propodeum coarsely reticulaterugose (
<figureCitation box="[887,980,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron evenly convex, coarsely reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[355,443,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,907,933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Wings.</emphasis>
Length of fore wing 2.9 × its width; length of marginal cell 1.3 × pterostigma; r: 3-SR: SRl= 9: 9: 43; SRl straight; parastigma distinctly swollen; 1-CU1: 2-CU1= 10: 27 (
<figureCitation box="[918,1009,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,979,1005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind coxa completely smooth and punctate; hind femur pretty robust; length of hind femur, tibia and basitarsus 3.1 ×, 5.2 × and 4.75 × their maximum width, respectively.
</paragraph>
