<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Carapace elongate-oval, a narrow lamella dorsally of apical carapace in dorsal view, posterior part of carapace with transversely curved deepened furrow; length of carapace 2.6 × its maximum width in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[159,253,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); ventral cavity completely open to apex; ovipositor extended beyond apex of metasomal carapace and covered with a semi-round and semi-hyaline short lamella, ovipositor slender and the ovipositor sheath 0.11 × as long as fore wing, 0.32 × as long as hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[678,766,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chelonus (Arichelonus) kenosetrus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, dorsal aspect; E, metasoma, lateral aspect; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, head, lateral aspect; I, antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854036" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854036/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,330,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Colour.</emphasis>
Black; antennomeres blackish-brown; pterostigma and veins blackish-brown; fore wing more or less darkened; metasoma entirely brown; legs almost entirely yellowish-brown; ovipositor sheath brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" box="[199,1221,402,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,402,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Variation.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[470,607,402,429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="6" pageNumber="533" unit="mm" value="4.15" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="3.7">3.7–4.6 mm</quantity>
, and length of ovipositor 0.2–0.4 × of carapace length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" box="[199,392,438,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,438,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
