<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,510,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">Etymology.</emphasis>
From 
<emphasis box="[412,476,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">kenos</emphasis>
(Greek for empty) and 
<emphasis box="[748,806,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="533">etron</emphasis>
(Greek for belly) because its ventral cavity completely open to the apex.
</paragraph>
